<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEVERAL FORD MODELS RECALLED DUE TO EMISSIONS PROBLEMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DEARBORN, Mich. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ford Motor Co. on Monday recalled 64,115 cars and light trucks because of 
emission system problems. 
</P>
<P>
The company said it was recalling 64,000 1986 model Lincoln Town Cars, 
Continentals and Mark VIIs; Ford Crown Victoria, Thunderbird and Mustang; 
Mercury Grand Marquis, Cougar and Capri, and some 1987 Lincoln Mark VII cars 
with 5-liter or 5-liter, high-output engines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
